text:
As it has been announced the status team is switching to its new workflow and the the following few things are necessary:

- the https://github.com/freebsd/freebsd-quarterly repository is not needed any more and should be archived;

- I think the freebsd/quarterly GitHub team is not needed any more. It might still be useful if it is possible to set the team as reviewer or assignee for a freebsd/freebsd-doc pull request, but it seems to me that it is not possible. If it is not, we can remove the GitHub team. We can also keep it as it should not hurt, but if we do, it would be better to rename it to freebsd/status for consistency;

- I would like to label pull requests meant for status reports with a "status reports" label, but I do not seem to be able to create the label. This is probably due to the fact that I lack some privilege on the freebsd/freebsd-doc GitHub repository. May I ask you to create the "status reports" label please?

Merging pull request should be done through the procedure described in https://docs.freebsd.org/en/articles/committers-guide/#github-pull-land , isn't it? And this does not need any write access to the GitHub freebsd/doc repository, is that right? If I am wrong and write access is necessary, it should be ensured that members of the status team (debdrup, pauamma and myself) all have that access.

Thanks.
